</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Document sharing sites for backlinks organized by content type and domain authority" src="/images/blog/document-sharing-sites-by-category.webp" /></p>
<h2>PDF Submission Sites for Backlinks</h2>
<p>PDF submission sites are the foundation of document sharing link building. You upload a PDF version of your content. The platform hosts it and links back to your website from your profile or the document description. Most accept free uploads.</p>
<p><strong>1. <a href="https://www.scribd.com">Scribd</a>. DA 96, 100M+ Users</strong></p>
<p>Scribd is the largest document sharing platform on the internet. It hosts books, audiobooks, PDFs, and presentations for over 100 million users. The DA is 96.</p>
<p>Upload a PDF with your website URL in the document footer and profile bio. Description links are nofollow. The in-document links remain clickable. Scribd PDFs get indexed by Google and often rank for long-tail keywords. That means your uploaded PDF can drive organic traffic directly, in addition to the <a href="/glossary/backlinks/">backlink</a> value from your profile page.</p>
