<h2>PPT Submission Sites for Backlinks</h2>
<p>Presentation sharing platforms accept slide decks and link back to your website from your profile. Converting a blog post into a 15-20 slide presentation takes less than an hour. The backlink value lasts years.</p>
<p><strong>6. <a href="https://www.slideshare.net">SlideShare</a>. DA 92, 70M+ Monthly Visitors</strong></p>
<p>SlideShare is the gold standard for presentation sharing. LinkedIn owns it. The DA is 92, and the platform attracts 70 million+ monthly visitors. That combination of authority and traffic is hard to beat.</p>
<p>Profile links are nofollow. SlideShare presentations rank in Google for competitive keywords. A well-optimized slide deck with your target keyword in the title, description, and tags can drive hundreds of monthly visitors. Include your website URL on the first and last slides. Add it in the presentation description. SlideShare remains one of the highest-value <a href="/blog/content-distribution-guide/">content distribution</a> channels for B2B companies.</p>
<p><strong>7. <a href="https://speakerdeck.com">SpeakerDeck</a>. Clean, Developer-Friendly</strong></p>
<p>SpeakerDeck is owned by GitHub. It provides a clean, minimal interface for hosting presentation slides. The platform attracts a technical audience of developers, engineers, and startup founders.</p>
<p>Upload PDFs of your slide decks. Your profile includes a website link. SpeakerDeck presentations load fast and embed cleanly on other websites. The developer audience makes this platform especially valuable for SaaS companies, dev tools, and technical content. Less competition than SlideShare means higher visibility for your uploads.</p>
<p><strong>8. <a href="https://prezi.com">Prezi</a>. Dynamic Presentations</strong></p>
<p>Prezi replaces linear slide decks with zooming, dynamic presentations. The platform has high domain authority and attracts millions of users worldwide.</p>
<p>Free accounts allow public presentations that include your profile link. Prezi presentations stand out visually. They get shared more often than standard slide decks. Convert your best <a href="/blog/how-to-write-seo-blog-posts/">blog post content</a> into a Prezi presentation for a unique backlink source that doubles as a marketing asset.</p>
<p><strong>9. <a href="https://www.slideserve.com">SlideServe</a>. Quick Upload, Fast Indexing</strong></p>
<p>SlideServe accepts PowerPoint uploads and converts them into embeddable slideshows. The platform has decent domain authority and fast indexing times.</p>
<p>Upload your presentation with keyword-optimized title and description. Your profile includes a website URL field. SlideServe presentations get indexed by Google within days. The platform supports PDF and PPT formats. Less well-known than SlideShare, which means less competition for keyword rankings within the platform.</p>
<h2>Infographic Submission Sites for Backlinks</h2>
<p>Infographics earn 25.8% more backlinks than videos and how-to articles, according to <a href="https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking">content format studies</a>. Submitting infographics to dedicated directories amplifies that advantage.</p>
<p><strong>10. <a href="https://www.behance.net">Behance</a>. DA 94, Adobe-Owned</strong></p>
<p>Behance is Adobe's creative portfolio platform with a DA of 94 and 10 million+ members. Designers dominate, but any business can create a profile. Upload infographics, data visualizations, or branded graphics to earn a backlink.</p>
<p>Your project pages include a link to your website. Behance projects rank well in Google Image search. The Adobe brand association adds credibility. Upload your infographics as projects with keyword-rich titles, descriptions, and tags. Behance works as both a <a href="/blog/build-citation-worthy-brand/">brand authority</a> builder and a backlink source.</p>
<p><strong>11. <a href="https://www.pinterest.com">Pinterest</a>. DA 94, Visual Search Engine</strong></p>
<p>Pinterest has a DA of 94 and functions as a visual search engine with 450 million+ monthly active users. Every pin you create includes a link back to your website.</p>
<p>Links are nofollow. The traffic value compensates. Pins with infographics get repinned and shared across the platform. A single infographic pin can drive traffic for years. Create a Pinterest board for your industry and pin each infographic with a keyword-optimized description and a link to the <a href="/blog/repurpose-blog-content-social-media/">original blog post</a>.</p>
<p><strong>12. <a href="https://dailyinfographic.com">Daily Infographic</a>. DA 74, Dedicated Directory</strong></p>
<p>Daily Infographic is a curated infographic directory with a DA of 74. The site publishes 1-3 infographics per day and links back to the source.</p>
<p>Free submissions take about 90 days to publish. Paid options expedite the process. The editorial team reviews each submission for quality. Accepted infographics receive a dedicated post page with a backlink to your site. This is one of the few infographic directories that provides editorial context around your visual content.</p>
<p><strong>13. <a href="https://infographicjournal.com">Infographic Journal</a>. DA 70, Editorial Reviews</strong></p>
<p>Infographic Journal curates and publishes infographics with editorial commentary. The DA is 70. Free submissions take 2-3 weeks. Express publishing costs $25. Featured placement costs $75.</p>
<p>Each accepted infographic gets its own page with your backlink, social sharing buttons, and editorial description. The editorial approach gives your infographic more credibility than a simple directory listing. Infographic Journal accepts infographics from all industries.</p>
