<h2>Video Submission Sites for Backlinks</h2>
<p>Video hosting platforms provide backlinks through channel profiles and video descriptions. <a href="/blog/video-marketing-statistics/">Video marketing statistics</a> show that video content drives more engagement than any other format. The backlink value is a bonus on top of the traffic.</p>
<p><strong>14. <a href="https://www.youtube.com">YouTube</a>. DA 100, 2B+ Users</strong></p>
<p>YouTube has a DA of 100. No other backlink source matches that authority score. Every YouTube channel includes a website link on the "About" page. Video descriptions support clickable URLs.</p>
<p>Description links are nofollow. The indirect SEO benefits are massive. YouTube videos rank in Google universal search results. A video optimized for your target keyword can appear on page 1 of Google alongside your blog post. Add your website URL in the first 2 lines of every video description. Links placed below the fold require viewers to click "show more."</p>
<p><strong>15. <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>. DA 96, Professional Quality</strong></p>
<p>Vimeo has a DA of 96 and positions itself as the premium alternative to YouTube. The platform attracts 50 million+ users who value production quality over viral content.</p>
<p>Your profile page includes a website link. Video descriptions support URLs. Vimeo's ad-free environment gives your content a more professional appearance. The platform also provides embeddable video players that load faster than YouTube embeds. For B2B companies and SaaS products, Vimeo carries stronger <a href="/blog/brand-mentions-vs-backlinks/">brand signals</a> than YouTube.</p>
<p><strong>16. <a href="https://www.dailymotion.com">Dailymotion</a>. DA 95, 300M+ Monthly Users</strong></p>
<p>Dailymotion has a DA of 95 and reaches 300 million+ monthly users. The platform is popular in Europe and expanding globally.</p>
<p>Channel profiles include a website link. Video descriptions support URLs. Dailymotion has less competition than YouTube, which means your videos are more likely to surface in platform search results. Upload the same videos you publish on YouTube. The additional backlink from a DA 95 domain costs nothing but a few minutes of upload time.</p>
<p><strong>17. <a href="https://rumble.com">Rumble</a>. Growing Alternative</strong></p>
<p>Rumble is a growing video platform with increasing domain authority. The platform positions itself as a free speech alternative to YouTube and attracts a different audience demographic.</p>
<p>Channel profiles include website links. Rumble's growing user base means your videos reach audiences that might not find you on YouTube. The platform accepts all video formats and lengths. Cross-posting from YouTube takes minutes.</p>
<h2>Podcast Directories for Backlinks</h2>
<p>Podcast directories provide backlinks through show profiles. You do not need a weekly show. Even a monthly or quarterly podcast earns directory backlinks that stay active as long as your feed exists. <a href="https://www.buzzsprout.com/blog/podcast-directories">Spotify and Apple Podcasts control about 70% of listener share</a> combined.</p>
<p><strong>18. <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com">Apple Podcasts</a> ,  33% of All Downloads</strong></p>
<p>Apple Podcasts accounts for 33.2% of all podcast downloads worldwide. Submitting your podcast requires an RSS feed and takes 24-48 hours for approval.</p>
<p>Your show page includes a link to your website. Apple Podcasts supports transcripts and chapter markers that improve discoverability. The Apple brand association adds authority signals. Every episode with show notes creates an indexed page that can rank in Google. This is one of the highest-value podcast directories for SEO.</p>
<p><strong>19. <a href="https://podcasters.spotify.com">Spotify</a> ,  35% of All Downloads</strong></p>
<p>Spotify is the most popular podcast platform with 35.4% of all downloads. Submit through Spotify for Podcasters (formerly Anchor).</p>
<p>Your show profile includes a website link. Spotify's recommendation algorithm surfaces podcasts to relevant listeners. Episode descriptions support text that gets indexed. The combination of massive reach and a DA 90+ backlink makes Spotify essential for any <a href="/blog/content-marketing-strategy/">content marketing strategy</a>.</p>
<p><strong>20. <a href="https://www.listennotes.com">Listen Notes</a>. The Podcast Search Engine</strong></p>
<p>Listen Notes is a dedicated podcast search engine that indexes over 3 million podcasts. The platform functions like Google but exclusively for audio content.</p>
<p>Your podcast show page includes a website link and episode-level pages with full descriptions. Listen Notes pages rank well in Google for podcast-related queries. The platform also provides an API that other apps use, which means your podcast metadata propagates across the ecosystem.</p>
<p><strong>21. <a href="https://www.podchaser.com">Podchaser</a>. IMDb for Podcasts</strong></p>
<p>Podchaser calls itself the "IMDb for podcasts." The platform lets listeners rate, review, and track podcasts. Creators claim their show profiles and add website links.</p>
<p>Podchaser profiles include detailed metadata that helps search engines understand your podcast's topic and authority. The platform's review system adds social proof. Cross-linking your Podchaser profile from your website creates a bidirectional trust signal.</p>
<p><strong>22. <a href="https://podcastindex.org">Podcast Index</a>. Open-Source Directory</strong></p>
<p>Podcast Index is an open-source, community-driven podcast directory. It serves as the backend for many third-party podcast apps.</p>
<p>Submit your RSS feed for free. Your show page includes a website link. Because Podcast Index feeds data to dozens of smaller podcast apps, one submission propagates your podcast (and backlink) across multiple platforms simultaneously.</p>
